<section class="text-block">
  <h3 class="text-block_title">Solution</h3>
  <p class="text-block_copy">I started by conducting many user interviews with our lead UX expert. Together we documented our current customer's userflow and worked out how our changes would impact this flow. We also looked at online articles and forumns written by current and ex-customers. It was eye-opening to see the workarounds our users had created and shared to solve the problems that Campaigns would ultimately fix.</p>

  <p class="text-block_copy">The end result was <a href="http://www.aweber.com/campaigns.htm" target="_blank">Campaigns</a>, an automated email platform with a sleek new drag and drop editor, to a help customers easily create manage multiple email campaigns from one interface. With Campaigns, our users are able to create automated email conversations with the context needed to cut through the clutter. I led the design process from workflow and wireframes to production implementation. Read more about the feature announcement <a href="https://blog.aweber.com/new-features/introducing-campaigns-your-new-email-automation-platform.htm" target="blank">here</a>.</p>
